Msambweni MP Suleiman Dori has maintained the ODM primaries were free and fair, saying there is no need to repeat the exercise.He criticised his closest rival Omar Boga for alleging he was rigged out. Boga, who has applied to run as an independent candidate, said the nominations did not take place at Bongwe/Gombato ward, one of his strongholds.Speaking during a function at his home yesterday, Dori said the exercise was progressing well in the ward until some individuals burnt ballot boxes. He said the primaries were peaceful.&ldquo;I am ready to accept defeat in the coming general election if luck is not on my side,&rdquo; the MP said. Boga said he has quit ODM and Dori should keep off the issue.